text: 19 to 20 is the debut extended play by South Korean singer Jimin Park, released on August 23, 2016 by JYP Entertainment. ==Background and release== On August 10, JYP Entertainment confirmed that Park Jimin currently prepared her comeback in mid-August. On August 16, Jimin dropped teaser image for her comeback with title track ″Try″, which set to be released on August 23. On August 19, the music video teaser for title track was released and confirmed to released album titled ″19 to 20″ on August 23. ==Track listing== All tracks co-written and co-composed by Park Ji-min. ==Release history== {|class="wikitable" ! style="text-align:center;"| Region ! style="text- align:center;"| Date ! style="text-align:center;"| Format ! style="text- align:center;"| Label |- | style="text-align:center;"| Worldwide | style="text-align:center;" rowspan=3| August 23, 2016 | rowspan=2|Digital download | rowspan=2|JYP Entertainment |- | style="text-align:center;"|South Korea |- | style="text-align:center;"|South Korea | CD | JYP Entertainment, KT Music |} ==References== Category:2016 EPs Category:JYP Entertainment EPs Category:Korean-language EPs Category:Genie Music EPs
